I stopped by on a day where they were having a test drive event along with free food like burgers and hot dogs.  What a complete waste of time. They completely ignored me when I walked in. For the 15 minutes I was walking around and looking at the scooters, they didn't even bother to ask if I had any questions or if I wanted a test drive. They were more interested in talking to each other and their friends that were just there hanging out.   I thought the idea of running a business is to make money. Perhaps I am sorely mistaken because it seems like they didn't want any customers bothering them during their conversations.  When I decide to purchase a scooter, I will go look elsewhere even if I have to drive across town. I suggest you do the same and take heed of all the rest of the bad reviews for this "business."

