mWTFbL-ilQiQ9iQwPnViQw
Great little whole in the wall restaurant on the west side of town which I don't frequent often.  We had a group of friends gather here to try out their Caribbean cuisine. Due to traffic and a few snafus we didn't arrive until past closing time. They were kind enough to keep their kitchen open for our group of 10.  I ordered the sample platter and the jerk chicken. Little did I know the sample platter also had jerk chicken on it, along with buffalo wings, fries, and doughnut holes. The jerk chicken plate came with rice.  I would skip the sample platter for next time, but the jerk chicken was pretty good.  I'm looking forward to trying the other dishes next time.

